ong in the 1960s only to fade away in such a relatively short period of time, what caused NASA and the space program to languish throughout most of the 1970s only to reemerge in the 1980s, and, finally, what role the agency plays today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aAstronauticszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aSpace scienceszUnited StatesxHistory. 4aHistory : American History. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 4aPublic Policy : Public Policy. 4aScience, Mathematics, and Technology : Science and Technology. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / Astrophysics.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791483633423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791483633/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles